-- Acron May Receive VEB Financing for $2.82 Billion Potash Project
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2011-12-28T14:30:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/acron-may-receive-veb-financing-for-2-82-billion-potash-project.html
VEB, Russia’s state development
bank, may decide tomorrow on helping to fund OAO Acron’s $2.82
billion potash project, the government said.  Acron plans to produce 2 million metric tons of potash a
year at the Talitsky project, the government said said today in
an e-mailed statement. Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin  chairs the
VEB supervisory board.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
 yfedorinova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
